Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.63,0:12:01.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.90,0:12:06.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,this. key holder of the red horse that\NMr. Genda made was the start of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.97,0:12:10.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This red horse, that is supposed to\Nbring prosperous business...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.01,0:12:15.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know what caused\Nhe first fire in Rizencho,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.08,0:12:17.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but this horse was found\Nat the site of the fire because
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.85,0:12:22.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,e Owner oe use was\Na good customer of Mr. Genda's store...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.85,0:12:27.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Genda probably gave that person\Nthis key holder inside a box...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.79,0:12:30.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, before the person opened\Nthe box. the house caught fire...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.83,0:12:34.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The box and Kanu both burned leaving\Nbehind only the Red Rabbit Horse .
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.07,0:12:38.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course the owner of the house would\Nhave no knowledge of the horse
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.20,0:12:42.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Red Horse is a code word\Nfor the police meaning arsonist!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.44,0:12:44.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the press began making\Na fuss writing articles
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.21,0:12:46.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,such as "The Start of a Series of Arsons. "...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.14,0:12:48.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the other hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.65,0:12:50.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr Genda who was shocked at\Nhearing the person saying
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.82,0:12:52.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,she knew nothing about\Nthe horse that he gave her...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.05,0:12:57.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,got worried that his sleepwalking habit\Nwhen he was a child had occurred again,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.66,0:13:02.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and went to your hospital,\Nwhere he was taken advantage of!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.03,0:13:05.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And. when you heard Genda's story.\NYou made him believe that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.60,0:13:09.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he was a sleepwalker who had a habit\Nof committing arsons...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.60,0:13:12.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and took note of the fact that\Nthe first fire occurred in 1 chome.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.07,0:13:16.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then after, you set fire to\N2-chome and 3-chome in order...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.47,0:13:18.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You burned your house on 4 chome,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.11,0:13:22.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and killed your wife, Ryoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.38,0:13:26.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You cut the Kanu and\Nstand off the key holder
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.12,0:13:28.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and left the red horse at the site of the fire
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.29,0:13:33.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to make it look like the serial arsonist did it,\Nand framed Mr. Genda up as the arsonist!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.06,0:13:38.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You made a spare key for\Nthis house and snuck in here
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.86,0:13:42.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,night after night to corner\NMr. Genda up against the wall
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.60,0:13:44.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You left shoe prints.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.27,0:13:47.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Burnt shirts and dirty socks in his room
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.30,0:13:50.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to make him come under\Nthe illusion that he was the arsonist!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.01,0:13:52.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.44,0:13:55.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Genda came of his own\Ninitiative to my hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.61,0:13:57.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,saying that he had a habit of sleepwalking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.05,0:13:59.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But. that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.42,0:14:01.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when he was a child. right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.05,0:14:05.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw on TV that there are many cases,\Nwhen a nervous child unable to cope with
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.89,0:14:10.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,all the excitement during the day\Nsleepwalks around at night!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.16,0:14:15.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A psychiatrist should know\Nsomething like that right off the bat, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.53,0:14:18.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But. Mr. Genda~was loitering around nearby
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.80,0:14:21.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when my house caught fire, wasn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.37,0:14:24.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would never know something like that,\Neven if I were his doctor, would I...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.24,0:14:30.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You heard Genda and Soga\Ntalking on the phone. didn't you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.18,0:14:33.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the wiretap that you set up inside\Nthe underside of the telephone
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.92,0:14:35.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that you took out a while ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.32,0:14:39.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After hearing Soga say. If you go\Nto the houses on that day]
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.46,0:14:43.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your fortune will take a turn for the better.\Nyou picked the date to set fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.13,0:14:49.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All you had to do was{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ge the beckoning\Ncat key holder Genda was supposed
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.95,0:14:52.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to pass out to the neighborhood\Nthat day. to the Red Rabbit Horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.74,0:14:55.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew that Mr. Genda would\Ncome to retrieve the key holders
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.54,0:14:57.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when he finds out that he had\Npassed out the wrong ones and that,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.98,0:15:01.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the people would become\Nsuspicious at seeing him do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.35,0:15:05.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it was the day that\NRyoko had called the detective,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.58,0:15:09.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you figured that if things worked out well,\Nthe detective would remember Genda
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.22,0:15:12.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.36,0:15:15.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fire was set at past 7:30 pm... right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.13,0:15:18.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Went out to drink with\NMr. Soga before 7:30 and
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.30,0:15:20.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he also testified to this!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.23,0:15:26.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or, ares ou saying the boy next door who\Ntestified to the time of the arson is lying?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.77,0:15:27.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.97,0:15:29.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.94,0:15:33.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The tissue paper is wrapped around\Nthe light bulb and taped on!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.78,0:15:36.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there's something poked in\Nbetween the tissue paper too!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.11,0:15:38.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.55,0:15:41.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Agh! It's a match!!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.57,0:15:45.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The surface temperature of a light bulb\Nof 100 watts is 218 degrees...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.66,0:15:47.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wrapping tissue paper around\Nsome ng I e a an
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.79,0:15:49.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,moreover, poking a match between it...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.59,0:15:51.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it's not hard to figure out\Nwhat will happen. is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.93,0:15:52.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.73,0:15:55.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it's a time-igniting device
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.67,0:16:00.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to set fire to your house while\Nyou are out drinking with Mr. Soga!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.60,0:16:04.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You did the same thing to\Nthe light bulb in the storeroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.04,0:16:06.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,poured kerosene on the floor
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.68,0:16:09.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and stuck a red horse between\Nthe window beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.28,0:16:12.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, before you went out drinking\Nwith Mr. Soga you turned on the light!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.82,0:16:16.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So. 10 minutes later, the match would ignite,\Nthe tissue paper would fall to the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.42,0:16:19.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and fire would break out...\NYou shouldn't do stuff like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.92,0:16:24.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the boy next door as usual\Nwatches TV with the room dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.75,0:16:27.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the tissue is wrapped\Naround the light bulb,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.20,0:16:30.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the light is still weak, so the silhouette\Nof the horse will not project.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.07,0:16:32.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But after the tissue paper burns off,\Nthe silhouette of the horse is projected
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.94,0:16:36.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as if the arsonist had left\Nthe horse behind at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.11,0:16:38.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You deliberately created this illusion!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.44,0:16:40.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next. you were probably\Nplanning to sneak in here
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.71,0:16:44.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and burn this place down: to erase\Ntraces of you having been here...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.62,0:16:46.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But. there is still other evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.02,0:16:50.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the stand of the key holder with\Nthe words Red Rabbit Horse on it that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.10,0:16:51.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ryoko was holding on\Nto at the time she died!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.62,0:16:57.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cut part matched the leg that\Nwas left back at the fire site on 3-chome
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.30,0:17:00.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now all that needs to be done,\Nis to see if the fingerprints that are on it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.93,0:17:04.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,match your fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.54,0:17:06.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You cut off the stand and Kanu because
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.90,0:17:09.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you didn't want anyone to know it\Nwas what Mr.-Genda had made.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.87,0:17:15.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't want him to get\Ncaught before you kill Ryoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.70,0:17:19.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems she knew what\Nyou were up to though.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.75,0:17:21.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She probably asked the detective\Nto come and investigate
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.99,0:17:25.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the suspicious person\NIoitering around at night
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.66,0:17:30.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but found out that it was you,\Nexperimenting on the trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.83,0:17:35.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After realizing it was you,\Nshe checked your belongings
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.07,0:17:37.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and found the red horse and the stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.37,0:17:40.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And was convinced that\Nthe serial arsonist was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.14,0:17:45.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She probably asked us to leave, because\Nshe was planning to threaten you to...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.74,0:17:47.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.14,0:17:49.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She threatened to divorce me\Nand kick me out of this house!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.11,0:17:51.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All I wanted to do was...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.57,0:17:54.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,burn the house and build a hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.29,0:17:56.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey. hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.72,0:17:58.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only if this stand wasn't found...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.89,0:18:00.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I didn't get deceived\Ninto a trap like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.73,0:18:03.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was supposed to be a perfect crime!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.43,0:18:05.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You fool,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.73,0:18:08.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we knew from before you came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.45,0:18:09.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't lie!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.83,0:18:11.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Soga could've done it and\Nso could Ryoko's older sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.14,0:18:12.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.20,0:18:16.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those two also sold objects\Nwith wiretaps in them to Genda
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.17,0:18:17.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and? ere wiretapping him...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.84,0:18:20.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They probably wanted him\Nto believe in Feng Shui
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.44,0:18:24.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and fortune-telling by telling\Nhim stuff only he alone knew,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.21,0:18:27.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and sell him more expensive stuff...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.85,0:18:32.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We found out from the telephone bill\Nthat the phone was wiretapped!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.64,0:18:35.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you wiretap\Nusing the telephone line,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.26,0:18:40.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it has to be connected all the while\Nso the telephone bill sky-rockets...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.93,0:18:44.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So. how can you tell that\NI'm the one who set it up?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.13,0:18:48.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could be either one of the two!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.47,0:18:50.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You still don't realize?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.24,0:18:50.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.61,0:18:54.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You understand that in order to\Nset up a wiretap in the phone
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.04,0:18:57.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you have to sneak into the house, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.65,0:18:59.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.82,0:19:01.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for the other two.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.19,0:19:03.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they were to sneak into the house
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.65,0:19:08.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,they would first of all remove the wiretap\Nfrom the things that they sold Mr. Genda,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.46,0:19:11.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because otherwise. they'd be suspected.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.40,0:19:18.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You probably came across\Ncommitting this crime
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.34,0:19:21.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,after reading Agatha Christie's\NThe ABC Murders but,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.37,0:19:25.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,\~why-didn't you realize then that\Nno matter how hard you think out the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.24,0:19:31.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who gets to laugh at\Nthe end is not the killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.52,0:19:35.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but the old man with the gray brain...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.73,0:19:51.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See you then, Mourn!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.90,0:19:53.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks for everythig.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.34,0:19:55.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H... no not at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.67,0:19:56.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...rather.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.64,0:19:59.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe I should be thanking these boys?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.35,0:20:05.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way...\NWhat will become of those two?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.22,0:20:05.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.62,0:20:11.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not that they sold something\Noutrageously expensive to Genda yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.35,0:20:13.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And all they did was sneak\NIn to collect their wiretaps
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.96,0:20:16.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because they didn't want to be\Nsuspected as arsonists, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.46,0:20:19.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll let them go after we give\Nthem a good lecture at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.13,0:20:25.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did you believe\NGenda was innocent...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.94,0:20:26.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.14,0:20:30.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Genda came up as a suspect,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.06,0:20:33.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I called him out to the park\Nand talked to him...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.74,0:20:36.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,stayed with him for 30 minutes,\Nbut he hardly talked
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.48,0:20:38.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, we decided to talk again\Nsome other time and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.95,0:20:41.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got up from the bench.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.99,0:20:44.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I turned to look back at him\Nfrom a distance... and saw him
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.02,0:20:48.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Iooking desperately for something\Nin the grassy area around the bench.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.23,0:20:54.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It began raining a little while\Nafter he left the bench...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.06,0:20:54.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It began raining a little while\Nafter he left the bench...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.80,0:20:57.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After seeing the look of relief on his face,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.10,0:20:59.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I finally understood...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.67,0:21:05.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that he was looking for the cigarette butt\Nthat I threw down on the ground...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.61,0:21:09.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because that was what caused\Nthe fire that took his father's life...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.72,0:21:15.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just couldn't believe that a guy like him\Ncould; set fireito anybody's house...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.92,0:21:18.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Neither:did I want believe he could...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.22,0:21:20.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's as simple as that...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.19,0:21:24.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See you... Mourn!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.86,0:21:26.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes sir
